{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1ba3ada9-070d-4050-a13f-b05f78ef268b","content":"Yes, you will run into compatibility issues. Your project targets three frameworks, and **two of them are not supported by MSTest v3**:\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped — .NET 5 is not supported; use `net6.0`+ |\n| `net462` | ❌ Dropped — .NET Framework < 4.6.2 is technically the cutoff, but `net462` *is* 4.6.2, so this one is actually fine ✅ |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped — .NET Core 3.1 is not supported; use `net6.0`+ |\n\nSo in practice, **`net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` must be replaced** (e.g., with `net6.0` or `net8.0`).\n\nBeyond target frameworks, common MSTest v3 breaking changes to watch for:\n- **`Assert.AreEqual`/`AreNotEqual` overload changes** — some generic overloads were tightened.\n- **`DataRow` constructor** — no longer accepts certain implicit conversions.\n- **Timeout behavior** — `[Timeout]` now uses `CancellationToken` by default instead of thread-abort.\n- **`.testsettings` files** — no longer supported; migrate to `.runsettings`.\n\nWould you like me to run the full migration skill to update your project automatically?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c465a473-902d-4707-9dec-3a7203cf9207","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a project targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They're using MSTest v2 (2.2.10). Let me invoke the MSTest v1/v2 to v3 migration skill since it's available and directly relevant.","outputTokens":446,"requestId":"D003:BBE67:5F4B85E:6B67300:69EC270D"},"id":"ebbfea03-750c-414b-8691-fb8c776fad0e","timestamp":"2026-04-25T02:29:42.881Z","parentId":"e2f72e09-021e-40eb-bc44-6433a193b920"}
